adwestro@ouray.denver.colorado.edu (Alan Westrope) writes:
: In article <2tv45e$4vt@lily.csv.warwick.ac.uk>, Bob Tinsley wrote:
: 
: > Do you have any suggestions for an introductory text to cryptanalysis?
: 
: I suspect the overwhelming majority of info on cryptanalysis is classified.
: You might look at _Military Cryptanalysis_, Part III and Part IV, published
: by Aegean Park Press, Laguna Hills, California.  I doubt that they're
: introductory in nature, since they were written by William Friedman, who
: directed the team that broke the Japanese "Purple" cipher in WWII.  The
: NSA only declassified them after John Gilmore filed a FOIA request and
: took them to court over their failure to respond.
: 
: If you do find an introductory text, please advise via email or this
: group!
: 
: 
